# Design Principles (SOLID)

Apply SOLID at **extension boundaries**; pragmatism is acceptable inside NautilusTrader lifecycle hooks (`on_start`, `on_bar`).

## Single Responsibility (S)

Each module should have one reason to change:

- `src/nt_ext/` ‚Äî trading extensions (strategies, risk rules, factories)
- `src/data_pipeline/` ‚Äî ingestion, normalization, catalog, bar loading
- `src/models/` ‚Äî ML/RL training, inference contracts, artifact loading
- `src/apps/` ‚Äî CLI entrypoints and orchestration only
- `src/analysis/` ‚Äî pure analytics on persisted results

Do not mix strategy logic, data I/O, persistence, and engine wiring in one function or class.

## Open/Closed (O)

Extend behavior via **registries** and **protocols**; avoid editing shared dispatchers:

- `STRATEGY_REGISTRY` in `src/nt_ext/factories.py` ‚Äî register new strategies; do not add `if spec.key == ...` branches to `build_strategy`.
- `MODEL_LOADERS` in `src/models/loader.py` ‚Äî register new model backends; apps must not import concrete model classes.
- `VENUE_CLIENT_FACTORIES` in `src/apps/live/node.py` ‚Äî register new venue clients; do not add `if venue.name == ...` in the main build path.
- `OrderRiskRule` protocol ‚Äî add new rule classes without changing existing ones.

## Liskov Substitution (L)

Subclasses must honor `BaseSignalStrategy` hooks (`register_indicators`, `on_signal_bar`). Do not monkey-patch child strategy attributes at runtime (no patching `portfolio`, `cache`, `enter_long`, etc.). Prefer composition: signal engines return intents; the parent owns order submission.

## Interface Segregation (I)

Keep protocols small and focused:

- `SignalModel.predict(features)` ‚Äî one method, numpy in/out
- `OrderRiskRule.check(ctx)` ‚Äî one method, `OrderContext` DTO
- `ModelLoader.load(artifact_path)` ‚Äî one method

Pass DTOs (`OrderContext`, feature arrays) into models and rules, not NautilusTrader engine objects.

## Dependency Inversion (D)

High-level modules depend on abstractions:

- Strategies depend on `SignalModel`, not `JaxSignalModel`
- Apps depend on `load_signal_model()` and `build_strategy()`, not concrete implementations
- Concrete wiring lives only in `nt_ext/factories`, `models/loader`, and `apps/live/node`

## Import boundaries

| Layer | May import | Must not import |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `apps/` | protocols, factories, config, data_pipeline public API | `models.jax_signal`, concrete strategy classes |
| `nt_ext/strategies/` | `models.inference.SignalModel`, risk protocols | JAX, venue clients, secrets |
| `models/inference.py` | numpy only | JAX, NautilusTrader |

## Review checklist

Apply on every strategy, risk rule, model, factory, or data-pipeline change:

1. No new `if spec.key ==` or `if venue.name ==` branches in shared builders ‚Äî use a registry entry instead.
2. No concrete model imports outside `models/` and `nt_ext/factories`.
3. New risk rules implement `OrderRiskRule`; new models implement `SignalModel`.
4. Unit tests use fake protocol implementations where applicable.
5. `make lint test` passes for changed modules.
